item.title: Hello I need help with portforwarding a 317 rsps
item.dc:creator: @The_Web_Guy The Web Guy
item.description:
@The_Web_Guy wrote:

It doesn’t matter what revision of the server, 317, 474, 534, 608, 722, port-forwarding will always be port-forwarding. It’s very simple really.

  1. Start > Run–Type in ‘cmd’–
  2. In the black box/command prompt type in ‘ipconfig’
  3. Take note of the ‘IPV4’ address that is listed.
  4. Open your Web Browser and navigate to 192.168.1.1 (if that doesn’t work try; 192.168.0.1)
  5. Login, the default credentials are Username(admin); password(admin–Or password–).
  6. Navigate to your routers Port-forwarding options
  7. Enter in the IPV4 address as a new listing, select TCP and make it port 43594–Assuming your server is running on that port–
  8. Save the options and close out of your router settings.
  9. $$$ Profit
